REAL Housewives of Durban star and TV host, Nonkanyiso “LaConco” Conco has sent an appreciation post to all those who support her craft. In the same post, she lashed at those who speak ill of her. In her post she did not disclose any specific details but wrote: “Appreciation post. God, I can feel you giving me an experience of who you are. The more I rest in you, the greater it is. I’m grateful for it all. Ngiyabonga, Mhlengi wami.” “To my genuine friends who have supported my business, kwande, kukhanye kuwe ngokwenza okuhle kimi. I’m humbled and inspired by your love. I am proud to have you as my support system,” she wrote. ALSO READ : AYANDA’S NEW DOCCIE PUTS SPOTLIGHT ON GBV She further wrote: “Baphehli bodweshu ngegama lami ngiyabonga niyangiqinisa isisekelo sempilo yami siyangokuqina nomdali uzoya ngokunikhombisa ngingowakhe” loosely translated as “Those who speak ill of me are only encouraging me to do more. My God will show you that I’m his child.” Her fans took turns comforting and encouraging her. Zizo Majeke commented: “May God continue to shower you with tons of blessings. Please stay genuine and stay as strong as you are. One thing I like about you is your smile, even when I’m watching Real Housewives of Durban. According to the ladies, you have the warmest hugs and that means you have a good heart. Thanks a lot for entertaining us and remain blessed.” Precious Lindokuhle Mokoena commented: “Having you as a role model boosts my confidence. I nearly gave up on achieving my goals but now you gave me hope. I even registered my own company. Thank you, Mngeee.” Nolutsha Hlaluminathi Nxopho wrote: “I just love you. Keep queening. Your confidence is contagious. Please don’t change, stay authentic and beautiful as you are.” 